Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 186,.proposition: This is a civil action brought by the Plaintiff, Jessica Wallis, against the Defendant, Mark Thompson, arising from the Defendant's breach of the covenant of quiet enjoyment as set forth under Massachusetts General Laws, Chapter 186, § 14.

G.L. c. 218, \u00a7 19.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction over this matter pursuant to G.L. c. 218, § 19, as the amount in controversy does not exceed $50,000.

G.L. c. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: Pursuant to G.L. c. 186, § 14, every residential lease in Massachusetts includes an implied covenant of quiet enjoyment, which protects the tenant's right to peaceful use and enjoyment of the premises without substantial interference by the landlord or their agents.
